--------------------------------------------------------------
   =======================================================
   MEIGA - Simulations Framework for Astroparticle Physics
   =======================================================

                       G4ExSimulator
                       -------------
--------------------------------------------------------------


Example Application of the Meiga Framework. This application 
is intended for testing after compilation and orienting users 
through the framework usage.

_How to run_
After compilation, in the application directory run the
executable with a configuration file:

./G4ExSimulator -c G4ExSimulator.json

- DetectorList.xml:
Example detector configuration for this application using
a simple scintillator detector of 12 plastic bars. 
Detector construction in src/G4Models/Scintillator.cc
Just plastic bars with corresponding scintillator properties.
No optical fibers or optical devices.

- G4ExSimulator.json:
Standard configuration of the application. 
* Input: single muon of 1 GeV of energy
* Output: save input particle information and deposited energy
	in the detector. PETime and charge not available since no
	optical device is present in this example detector.
* TrajVisOn / GeoVisOn: if true, 3D render file with particle
	trajectory and detector geometry will be built.